org.chronos.chronograph.api.index

Interface ChronoGraphIndex

  • All Known Subinterfaces:
    ChronoGraphIndexInternal, IChronoGraphEdgeIndex, IChronoGraphVertexIndex
    All Known Implementing Classes:
    AbstractChronoGraphIndex, AbstractChronoGraphIndex2, ChronoGraphEdgeIndex, ChronoGraphEdgeIndex2, ChronoGraphVertexIndex, ChronoGraphVertexIndex2

    public interface ChronoGraphIndex
    Specifies metadata about an existing graph index.

    Instances of this class are created when a new index is specified via the fluent builder API in ChronoGraphIndexManager.create(). All existing instances can be queried by using the graph index manager methods, e.g. ChronoGraphIndexManager.getAllIndices().
